-- CR Enterprise shares down 6 pct after parent chief probe
-- By Donny Kwok and Lee Yimou
-- Mon Apr 21, 2014 10:20PM EDT
-- None



HONG KONG, April 22 (Reuters) - Shares of retail focused China Resources Enterprise Ltd <0291.HK> fell as much as 6.1 percent on Tuesday morning after Chinese authorities said they were probing the head of its parent group, while selling pressure spread to other units.

China Resources Enterprise trimmed its losses to HK$21.90 as at 0148 GMT, but the stock was still down 4.2 percent, heading to its biggest drop since February 25. That compared to a 0.2 percent gain in the benchmark Hang Seng Index <.HSI>. Shares in other Hong Kong-listed companies under the parent group were also under selling pressure. China Resources Power Co Ltd <0836.HK> dived more than 11 percent, China Resources Land Ltd <1109.HK> slid 2.5 percent and China Resources Cement Holdings Ltd <1313.HK> was down 5.9 percent.